Question 1: Declare three variables (age, height, gender) and initialize them with appropriate values. Print the values of these variables.

          public class VariableExample {
              public static void main(String[] args) {
                  // Declare and initialize variables
                  int age = 25;
                  double height = 5.9;
                  char gender = 'M';

                  // Print variables
                  System.out.println("Age: " + age);
                  System.out.println("Height: " + height);
                  System.out.println("Gender: " + gender);
              }
          }


Question 2: Explore implicit and explicit type (Datatype) conversions in Java. Explain the output of the program.

         public class TypeConversionExample {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Implicit type conversion
                 int numInt = 10;
                 double numDouble = numInt;

                 // Explicit type conversion
                 double doubleNum = 20.5;
                 int intNum = (int) doubleNum;

                 // Print converted values
                 System.out.println("Implicit Conversion: " + numDouble);
                 System.out.println("Explicit Conversion: " + intNum);
             }
         }


Question 3: Declare two strings (firstName and lastName) and concatenate them to form the full name. Print the full name.

         public class StringConcatenationExample {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Concatenate strings
                 String firstName = "John";
                 String lastName = "Doe";
                 String fullName = firstName + " " + lastName;

                 // Print full name
                 System.out.println("Full Name: " + fullName);
             }
         }

Question 4: Write a program that takes the user's age as input and prints it. Test the program with different age inputs.

         import java.util.Scanner;

         public class UserInputExample {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Get user input
                 Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
                 System.out.print("Enter your age: ");
                 int age = scanner.nextInt();

                 // Print user input
                 System.out.println("Your Age: " + age);

                 // Close scanner
                 scanner.close();
             }
         }


Question 5: Declare and initialize an array of integers. Calculate and print the sum of the array elements.

         public class ArraySum {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Declare and initialize an array of integers
                 int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};

                 // Calculate the sum of array elements
                 int sum = 0;
                 for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
                     sum += numbers[i];
                 }

                 // Print the sum
                 System.out.println("Sum of Array Elements: " + sum);
             }
         }


Question 6: Declare two variables a and b. Use relational operators to compare the values of a and b. Print the results.

         public class RelationalOperators {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Declare two variables
                 int a = 5;
                 int b = 10;

                 // Use relational operators to compare values
                 System.out.println("a < b: " + (a < b));
                 System.out.println("a > b: " + (a > b));
                 System.out.println("a <= b: " + (a <= b));
                 System.out.println("a >= b: " + (a >= b));
                 System.out.println("a == b: " + (a == b));
                 System.out.println("a != b: " + (a != b));
             }
         }

Question 7: Declare two boolean variables x and y. Use logical operators to combine boolean values. Print the results.

         public class LogicalOperators {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Declare two boolean variables
                 boolean x = true;
                 boolean y = false;

                 // Use logical operators to combine boolean values
                 System.out.println("x && y: " + (x && y));
                 System.out.println("x || y: " + (x || y));
                 System.out.println("!x: " + (!x));
             }
         }

Question 8: Declare three boolean variables a, b, and c. Evaluate the expression a && b || c and print the result.

         public class LogicalAndPrecedence {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Declare three boolean variables
                 boolean a = true;
                 boolean b = false;
                 boolean c = true;

                 // Evaluate the expression with logical AND
                 boolean result = a && b || c;

                 // Print the result
                 System.out.println("Result: " + result);
             }
         }

Question 9: Declare three boolean variables x, y, and z. Evaluate the expression x || y && z and print the result.

         public class LogicalOrPrecedence {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Declare three boolean variables
                 boolean x = true;
                 boolean y = false;
                 boolean z = true;

                 // Evaluate the expression with logical OR
                 boolean result = x || y && z;

                 // Print the result
                 System.out.println("Result: " + result);
             }
         }

Question 10: Declare a boolean variable p. Evaluate the expression !p || p && !p and print the result.

         public class LogicalNotPrecedence {
             public static void main(String[] args) {
                 // Declare a boolean variable
                 boolean p = true;

                 // Evaluate the expression with logical NOT
                 boolean result = !p || p && !p;

                 // Print the result
                 System.out.println("Result: " + result);
             }
         }
